Does entire village does not get water supply?

In [60]:
### Column Name
col_1='Do you have water supply to your house/TBR ?'

### Create a column to identify whether the household does not receive water
raw_data['% of Households with No Water Supply'] = pd.to_numeric(
    raw_data[col_1].apply(lambda x: 100.00 if (x=="No") else 0))

### Create a Pivot % of such households village wise 
villages_with_no_supply = raw_data.pivot_table(index = ['District','Block','Gram Panchayat','Village'],
                    values = ['% of Households with No Water Supply'],
                    aggfunc = {'% of Households with No Water Supply':np.mean}
                    )

### Binning the number of villages into % of households not receiving water
bins = [0, 1, 5, 10, 25, 50, 100]
villages_with_no_supply['Binned']=pd.cut(villages_with_no_supply['% of Households with No Water Supply'],bins)

display_bar(df=villages_with_no_supply['Binned'].value_counts(),
            title='Number of Villages by % of Households not receiving water)',
           size=[7,5])

Observation:
